# start work
git checkout dsa/TrollStability
git add / commit frequently
git push origin dsa/TrollStability

# integrate main only when necessary
git fetch origin
git merge origin/main   # safe and easy
# or
git rebase origin/main  # clean history, requires force push

# push branch after resolving conflicts
git push --force-with-lease origin dsa/TrollStability


supposedly can use this to bring in updates from remote/main :

git fetch origin && \
git checkout main && git pull origin main && \
git checkout dsa/TrollStability && \
git merge main

the rebase version:

git fetch origin && \
git checkout main && git pull origin main && \
git checkout dsa/TrollStability && \
git rebase main && \
git push --force-with-lease origin dsa/TrollStability

#________________________________________________________

1) Check GIT status
	git status
	
2) If there are modified files from status check
	git commit -am "WIP: save before syncing main"
	or
	git stash
	
3) Switch to main, update it
	git switch main
	git pull -ff-only origin main
	
4) 